    "Their architecture enables the propagation of information across a sequence by maintaining an internal hidden state.",
    "This allows RNNs to capture dependencies and patterns from previous states, influencing the decisions made at subsequent states.",
    "where X t ∈ R n×d is an input at time step t, H t ∈ R n×h is the hidden layer output of time step t, H t-1 is the hidden layer output from previous time step and O t is the output at time step t. W xh ∈ R d×h, W hh ∈ R h×h, and W ho ∈ R h×o are the learnable weights of the input, hidden state and output layer respectively.",
    "b h ∈ R 1×h and b o ∈ R 1×o are biases of the hid- den and the output layers, respectively.RNNs can suffer from the problems of vanishing and exploding gradients.",
    "To address these issues, a variant of RNN called Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) was introduced."
